## Context

- cdkn2a-pancancer-dependency-atlas: Completed Phase 3b MTAP-stratified genome-wide screen (task #1118, journal #1908).
- **MAJOR CORRECTION:** WDR77 and PRMT5 are MTAP-driven, NOT CDKN2A-specific. Both completely abolished after MTAP correction (d→0, FDR>0.95). 74.3% of CDKN2A-deleted lines have MTAP co-deletion.
- CDK6 CONFIRMED CDKN2A-specific (d=-0.508 after correction, stronger than original d=-0.453).
- WWTR1 (Hippo/TAZ) emerges as #1 CDKN2A-specific dependency (d=-0.845, FDR=2.4e-05).
- 23/55 (42%) original Phase 3 gained hits survived MTAP correction. 32/55 (58%) lost.
- Other strong CDKN2A-specific hits: KIF2C (d=-0.744), ZFP36L1 (d=-0.737), CRK (d=-0.722), SLC39A1 (d=-0.705), TLN1 (d=-0.628).
- Task #1231 created for RD to review MTAP-corrected findings and decide on novel finding labels.
- Task #1232 created for developer to regenerate Phase 1 CSV with MTAP columns.
- Phase 1 CSV is missing MTAP columns (code computes them but output was generated before MTAP code was added). Phase 3b loaded MTAP CN directly as workaround.
- Script: src/cancer/cdkn2a_pancancer_dependency_atlas/03b_mtap_stratified_screen.py
- Results: output/cdkn2a-pancancer-dependency-atlas/phase3b_mtap_stratified/
